Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.96,0:00:27.01,Sign,,0,0,0,,The Human Revolution {人間革命}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.75,0:00:27.01,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 10 \NDrive {推進}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.51,0:00:33.01,Sign,,0,0,0,,Original work: Daisaku Ikeda
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.01,0:00:37.03,Sign,,0,0,0,,January 1954
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.03,0:00:43.02,Sign,,0,0,0,,Shinanomachi Soka Gakkai Headquarters {信濃町・学会本部}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.82,0:00:43.02,NarTop,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai began its operations
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.02,0:00:51.24,NarTop,,0,0,0,,in 1954 with a goal of converting 80,000 households that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.04,0:00:51.86,Sign,,0,0,0,,Second President's Office {第二会長室}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.86,0:00:55.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,President Toda was focused on finding a way to accelerate
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.88,0:00:59.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai's progress towards \Nachieving the Common Path.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.01,0:01:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave that matter to you, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.06,0:01:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We got you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.05,0:01:10.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,Indeed, looking at the progress we've made over the past few years,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.32,0:01:14.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,you could say that the Soka Gakkai ship is running at full throttle,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.45,0:01:17.60,Thought,,0,0,0,,steadily sailing through the ocean of the Common Path. {/Gakkai Maru - maru is a suffix typical for ships}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.60,0:01:23.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,But in which direction should we steer Soka Gakkai to ensure it doesn't go off course?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.75,0:01:25.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's the #1 question.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.42,0:01:29.50,Thought,,0,0,0,,The ship can't move forward simply by revving its engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.50,0:01:31.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,To convert that into propulsion,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.13,0:01:34.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,you also need a sturdy screw.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.09,0:01:37.87,Thought,,0,0,0,,Engine, screw, and rudder... {actually "steering (a boat); helmsman" but the rest is objects so I think this fits more}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.41,0:01:45.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,Only when all three are in place \Ncan we sail safely straight to our destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.13,0:01:51.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,I've always though of myself \Nas the rudder of the Soka Gakkai ship,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.69,0:01:53.22,Thought,,0,0,0,,but upon reflection,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.72,0:01:57.14,Thought,,0,0,0,,I realize I've also been the screw.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.86,0:02:03.14,Thought,,0,0,0,,But what happens when that vital screw \Nbegins to wear out? {/age}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.91,0:02:07.08,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Common Path is bound to falter then. {/stall/lose momentum}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.08,0:02:10.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,What should we do about that screw \Nthat's supposed to propel the Common Path?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.96,0:02:16.16,Thought,,0,0,0,,If we don't start thinking about it now, \Nwe'll face a world of trouble later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.08,0:02:24.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,The propulsive force...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.93,0:02:33.11,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yes. That overflowing energy is what's going to become Soka Gakkai's propulsive force.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.30,0:02:39.57,Thought,,0,0,0,,What if we assigned a portion \Nof the Youth Department to each branch?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.57,0:02:45.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,We'd risk disuniting the Youth Division \Nand dispersing their strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.02,0:02:49.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,However, our youth can't keep growing if they have no place to apply what they've learned. {lit: place to work}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.71,0:02:54.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,If we do that, they could end up becoming the propulsive force for that branch. {これによって逆に支部の推進力になるともいえる やってみよう}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.28,0:02:56.74,Thought,,0,0,0,,Let's give it a try.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.49,0:03:06.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,But can we really expect the youth to become the propulsive force for all of Soka Gakkai
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.37,0:03:10.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,by simply placing one male and one female member in each branch?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.95,0:03:13.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm missing something.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.24,0:03:14.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,But what is it...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.26,0:03:19.26,Sign,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.18,0:03:21.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Focused on promoting education, Toda
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.26,0:03:23.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,Three Great Secret Laws {三重秘伝抄}{no idea what's this about, could be related to https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Three_Great_Secret_Laws}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.57,0:03:25.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,delivered a variety of lectures, primarily general ones
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.58,0:03:28.25,Narrator,,0,0,0,,at the Toshima Town Hall \Nthree days a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.25,0:03:33.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This fourth-level lecture, aimed at other educators, was one such example. {/for members of the teaching staff; no clue what's this "4 class/level" thing is, thinking maybe "for 4th year university students"; この教学部員を対象にした四級講義もその一つであった}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.78,0:03:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The Three Great Secret Laws, formulated by Nichikan Shonin,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.67,0:03:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,are the ultimate proof of the righteousness of Nichiren Daishonin's Buddhism
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.25,0:03:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that we believe in, \Nthe Lotus Sutra. {added to make it longer for better flow}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.29,0:03:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.60,0:03:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that should be all for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.52,0:03:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.55,0:04:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.02,0:04:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.41,0:04:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei! What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.58,0:04:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.31,0:04:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.42,0:04:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Irie-san, I believe Dr. Hayami is here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.77,0:04:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly call him over, but do it discreetly so as not to alarm everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.00,0:04:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.33,0:04:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, Hayami-san will be here soon, please stay strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.50,0:04:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayami-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.08,0:04:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's wrong with Sensei, please check on him immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.02,0:04:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.54,0:04:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Shin there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.86,0:04:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What? What did you say, Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.29,0:04:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin is not there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.32,0:04:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.36,0:05:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.92,0:05:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto-san was busy with work today.{and didn't come}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.30,0:05:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.05,0:05:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.37,0:05:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did Shin go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.97,0:05:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.06,0:05:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like a hypoglycemic attack. \NNo need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.69,0:05:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,When I make this injection,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.13,0:05:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the seizure will subside at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.14,0:05:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.11,0:05:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank god!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.64,0:05:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But to be on the safe side, \NI think it's best if he rests here tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.33,0:05:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.65,0:05:42.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,The harsh prison life
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.46,0:05:47.33,Thought,,0,0,0,,and the strain of the last ten years have taken a toll on my health.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.09,0:05:51.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,I might not have much time left to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.06,0:05:55.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,However, to lay the foundation for the future spread of the Common Path,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.56,0:06:00.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,I must accomplish my mission of converting 750,000 households, no matter what it takes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.68,0:06:03.69,Sign,,0,0,0,,Second President's Office {第二会長室}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.71,0:06:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.05,0:06:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,forgive me for being away last night. {wasn't really night, maybe "evening/afternoon"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.65,0:06:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you feeling now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.66,0:06:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.99,0:06:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin-Chan, let's lie down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.87,0:06:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You can use this as a pillow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.30,0:06:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one thing\Noccupying my mind right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.61,0:06:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't even gotten to the point where \NI'm ready to talk to someone about it yet, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.62,0:06:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, maybe even talking about it won't solve it. {もっとも相談してもしょうがないことかもしれない}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.21,0:06:38.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Sensei is acting strange tonight. Completely different from usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.48,0:06:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, you young men have to study harder than anyone else, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.63,0:06:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.69,0:06:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now is the important time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.01,0:06:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.01,0:06:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How is your health these days?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.56,0:06:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The success of the Common Path depends on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.58,0:06:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be more worried \Nfor yourself, Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.65,0:06:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,My own health?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.00,0:07:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't die just yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.00,0:07:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A creature such as man cannot die...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.70,0:07:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as he has work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.17,0:07:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, I'll do everything that needs to be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.34,0:07:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And as long as you study with all your might, \NI have no worries about the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.42,0:07:22.27,Thought,,0,0,0,,It seems like Sensei is trying to tell me something, but I don't understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.77,0:07:25.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,He said countless times that I must study,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.69,0:07:28.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,but what exactly is he getting at?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.32,0:07:35.20,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's right! I should let Shinichi \Nact as the screw in my stead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.73,0:07:41.11,Thought,,0,0,0,,For that to happen, we must first prepare a more fitting position for Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.73,0:07:43.86,Thought,,0,0,0,,What would that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.75,0:07:45.22,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.71,0:07:50.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,Rather than putting him in charge \Nof all of Soka Gakkai,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.51,0:07:57.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,we should first let Shinichi try his hand \Nat being a strong screw for the Youth Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.79,0:08:01.23,Thought,,0,0,0,,When the Youth move, \NSoka Gakkai moves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.23,0:08:05.80,Thought,,0,0,0,,We need to consider the circumstances \Nin which such a correlation would be valid... {lit: come up with a position when such diagram would be viable; そんな図式が成り立つような立場それを考えなくては･･･}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.80,0:08:12.98,Sign,,0,0,0,,{left to right}Caroline Islands {ロリン諸島}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.80,0:08:14.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,Enewetak Atoll
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.80,0:08:14.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,Bikini Atoll
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.80,0:08:14.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,Marshall Islands
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.27,0:08:12.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On March 1st,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.07,0:08:17.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the United States conducted a hydrogen bomb test at Bikini Atoll in the Pacific Ocean. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Castle_Bravo}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.53,0:08:22.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In the process, a Japanese tuna fishing boat, \Nthe Daigo Fukuryu Maru,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.36,0:08:25.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,which was operating outside the danger zone,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.08,0:08:32.58,Sign,,0,0,0,,23 Japanese fishermen caught up in Bikini hydrogen (?) bomb test {above; ビキニの水爆?実験で\N邦人漁夫二十三名被災}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.90,0:08:29.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was struck by heavy nuclear fallout \Nand became contaminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.42,0:08:33.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,All 23 crew members suffered from acute radiation syndrome,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.88,0:08:37.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and the entire tuna catch \Nhad to be discarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.60,0:08:43.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,One of the sailors later passed away due to complications from radiation sickness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.60,0:08:39.60,Sign,,0,0,0,,Do not touch! \NContaminated fish {手を触れるな\N原爆被客品}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.60,0:08:48.59,Sign,,0,0,0,,Toda
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.26,0:08:51.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,This is terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.36,0:08:55.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Japanese people became victims \Nof three atomic bombings:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.58,0:08:58.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,in Hiroshima, Nagasaki, \Nand now Bikini too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.10,0:08:58.12,Sign,,0,0,0,,{right} One person hospitalized with serious illness; University of Tokyo examines radioactive ash on the ship {名は重患で入院\N・船内の「降灰」東大で鑑定}\N{left} Ambassador Iguchi was telegraphed that it was outside the "danger zone" {井口大使に調査訓電\N問題は「危険水域通告}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.66,0:09:04.11,Thought,,0,0,0,,This time, there will be mass outrage all over Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.11,0:09:07.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,The world's brightest minds, like Einstein,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.83,0:09:11.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,warned us that a nuclear war would annihilate humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.46,0:09:14.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yet the leaders of the major powers \Nturn a deaf ear to that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.47,0:09:17.84,Thought,,0,0,0,,and continue developing these dangerous weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.84,0:09:23.48,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,It must be because they're fixated on the flawed belief that intimidating opponents
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.00,0:09:30.15,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,with overwhelming destructive force \Nwill deter war and lead to world peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.21,0:09:30.15,Sign,,0,0,0,,US President Eisenhower {アメリカ アイゼンハワー大統領}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.21,0:09:30.15,Sign,,0,0,0,,Soviet Union First Secretary Khrushchev {ソ連 ●フルシチョフ第一書記}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.15,0:09:34.15,Thought,,0,0,0,,Atomic and hydrogen weapons, \Nwhich lead humanity toward destruction,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.15,0:09:37.07,Thought,,0,0,0,,are truly the devil's handiwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.07,0:09:42.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,Fighting that won't be easy, \Nbut we gotta do whatever we can...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.20,0:09:45.52,NarTop,,0,0,0,,Toda's implacability at that moment
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.52,0:09:49.63,NarTop,,0,0,0,,would later culminate in the historic "Declaration for the Abolition
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.90,0:09:53.92,Sign,,0,0,0,,September 8th, 1957 \NPresident Toda delivers the "Declaration for the Abolition of Nuclear Weapons" at Mitsuzawa Stadium in Yokohama {1957年(昭和32年)9月8日\N横浜・三ッ沢競技場\N「原水爆禁止宣言」を発表する戸田会長}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.63,0:09:53.90,NarTop,,0,0,0,,of Nuclear Weapons," \Nwhich he delivered to the world from Yokohama.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.90,0:09:56.91,Sign,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.91,0:10:01.93,Sign,,0,0,0,,Interview Room{面接室}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.68,0:10:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.92,0:10:05.42,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suikokai Meeting {水滸会の会合}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.60,0:10:06.14,Top,,0,0,0,,an appeal for a ban on hydrogen bombs has been made in Suginami Ward,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.14,0:10:09.08,Top,,0,0,0,,and now they've launched a nationwide signature campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.08,0:10:11.92,Top,,0,0,0,,What should our stance on that be? {lit: how should we think about it}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.92,0:10:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm... I think it's commendable that the people have realized
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.61,0:10:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no future for mankind if we allow the nuclear weapons to go unchecked.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.93,0:10:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.94,0:10:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Watari-kun, you know the UNESCO Constitution, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.12,0:10:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.77,0:10:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In the preamble, it says...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.21,0:10:39.80,Sign,,0,0,0,,That since wars begin in the minds of men, it is in the minds of men that the defences of peace must be constructed; {from the background image}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.26,0:10:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Period. {/Like that/And so on}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.64,0:10:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And I agree with that. \NNo truer words have ever been spoken.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.04,0:10:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But the key question is how and with what materials we should
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.73,0:10:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,construct a bastion of peace in our hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.68,0:10:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's something...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.70,0:11:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we never tried to shed light on \Nin general discourse. {lit: no one has spoken clearly about this}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.01,0:11:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's intellectuals and leaders have not been able to clarify it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.54,0:11:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can answer that with full certainty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.77,0:11:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that could make this possible \Nis Nichiren Daishonin's great philosophy of life!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.87,0:11:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,By adhering to the teachings of Daishonin, who truly expounded the sanctity of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.14,0:11:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and by offering his prayer to the Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.55,0:11:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,one can become an angel or a demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.73,0:11:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We must transform humanity's fickle mind, \Nwhich is our entire life,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.10,0:11:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,into a firm and unwavering one \Nthat never ceases to desire absolute peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.76,0:11:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Only then can we build a bastion of peace in the hearts of all people that will never crumble!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.89,0:11:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.24,0:12:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Our nightly roundtable discussions,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.66,0:12:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,doctrinal lectures,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.24,0:12:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,conversion work, and personal tutoring
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.79,0:12:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,are humble activities, but they demand far more perseverance, study, and effort
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.88,0:12:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,than signature campaigns, as they comprise the life-transforming movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.32,0:12:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You, my friends, are the warriors, \Nwho stand on the front lines of this movement!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.20,0:12:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to keep that in mind at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.37,0:12:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.77,0:12:32.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,Toshima Town Hall, Ikebukuro {池袋・豊島公会堂}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.97,0:12:32.77,Top,,0,0,0,,By order of the president,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.77,0:12:36.50,Top,,0,0,0,,the following organizational changes \Nwill be implemented in the youth division:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.77,0:12:37.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,March 30th \NMarch Headquarters Executive Meeting {3月30日 3月度本部幹部会}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.50,0:12:39.38,Top,,0,0,0,,Establish a new detached office. {actually "staff room" but idk, maybe it's something more general like "reassemble the cabinet"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.38,0:12:43.78,Top,,0,0,0,,Appoint as the new division chief: \NYamamoto Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.57,0:12:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.38,0:12:50.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A committee was established to design \Nand draft all operational plans
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.66,0:12:57.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and educational policies aimed at advancing the Common Path and the religious revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.23,0:12:59.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto Shinichi was appointed as the department head,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.86,0:13:03.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,with Jujo Kiyoshi as the chief of staff,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.57,0:13:06.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,along with six other men and women.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.85,0:13:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,"I appoint the following department heads:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.80,0:13:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,1st Men's Division: Suzumoto Minoru..."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.07,0:13:21.19,NarTop,,0,0,0,,Additionally, a groundbreaking "one branch, one division" system was introduced,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.19,0:13:25.50,NarTop,,0,0,0,,assigning separate men's and women's divisions to all 15 branches.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.33,0:13:30.36,Sign,,0,0,0,,Chuo University Auditorium, Ochanomizu {御茶の水・中央大学講堂}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.36,0:13:34.34,Sign,,0,0,0,,April 29th \NYouth Division General Meeting {14月29日 青年部総会}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.48,0:13:39.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And then came the time for the Joint Youth General Meeting. {/Men's and Women's }
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.94,0:13:42.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Under President Toda's leadership,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.28,0:13:45.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,30 new division chiefs \Nfrom the men's and women's divisions
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.39,0:13:50.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,gathered in formation, ready to advance the progress of the Common Path.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.58,0:13:54.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,These young people became 30 screws,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.58,0:13:58.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,who are now going to propel their respective branches forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.40,0:14:03.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,The history of the Youth Division is unfolding right before our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.29,0:14:10.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,But I must not forget that this also \Nushers in a new era for me personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.56,0:14:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief Yamamoto! {actually "department head"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.39,0:14:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Jujo-san, let's hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.69,0:14:20.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Members of the Executive Staff
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.56,0:14:24.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,would often hurry to the Soka Gakkai headquarters after work
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.40,0:14:28.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and their missionary activities \Nto discuss various events and topics.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.05,0:14:28.56,Sign,,0,0,0,,Second reception room {第二応接室}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.01,0:14:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Department head, \NI'd like to confirm once again
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.99,0:14:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the intended role and planned activities of our movement. {lit: us the staff officers/advisers room" - whatever that means; it seems later they use it to simply to refer to soka gakkai or some of its parts}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.33,0:14:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.31,0:14:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, let's do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.98,0:14:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,As Sensei always says at Suikokai meetings,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.85,0:14:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe that the Common Path
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.13,0:14:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is about fighting to save the unfortunate people of Japan and the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.12,0:14:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.99,0:14:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,To achieve that, we need to develop a detailed and robust 100-year strategy
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.04,0:15:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that takes into account all the various problematic contingencies we may face.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.34,0:15:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, isn't it our responsibility to create a realistic and innovative plan
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.05,0:15:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to address the issues,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.88,0:15:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,starting with religion,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.32,0:15:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of politics, economy, ideology, culture, and education—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.97,0:15:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,essentially all the various challenges that impact people's lives—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.16,0:15:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,through the lens of Buddhist philosophy and under the guidance of Toda-sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.87,0:15:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.68,0:15:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Only by becoming the unsung heroes can we serve as the driving force that propels
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.07,0:15:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,all of Soka Gakkai and Youth Division activities forward. {I assume the terminology referencing the machinery is important in this episode}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.48,0:15:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.98,0:15:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, just a suggestion, why don't we put together a music band in the Youth Division?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.72,0:15:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Huh? Music band?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.72,0:15:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Revolutions always come with music. Why should our religious revolution be any different?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.99,0:16:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,A musical band performing at a youth event or meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.81,0:16:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,will lift the spirits of our ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.29,0:16:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe it will serve as a symbol of our youth's unity, and pave the way for a bright future.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.32,0:16:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I see! It's a great idea. \NIsn't it, Irie-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.33,0:16:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I think so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.90,0:16:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, we have Arimura-kun, a composer in the Men's Youth Division,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.78,0:16:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,so why not let him take charge of things?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.70,0:16:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.36,0:16:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I agree! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.14,0:16:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.34,0:16:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If everyone agrees, I'm going to ask Toda-sensei \Nfor his approval to form the band.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.47,0:16:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Please do!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.94,0:16:46.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda, who served as a counselor to Daito Trading,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.96,0:16:53.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,would come to the office every morning to consult and offer advice on business matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.94,0:16:46.96,Sign,,0,0,0,,Daito Trading {大東商工株式會社}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.84,0:16:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, may I have a minute of your time?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.58,0:16:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. Get seated first.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.17,0:17:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.81,0:17:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, I'd like to form a music band \Nwithin the Youth Division...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.15,0:17:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Music band?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.17,0:17:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, they will perform at all future youth meetings,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.14,0:17:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,bringing courage and hope \Nto everyone in attendance, I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.99,0:17:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.87,0:17:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I approve, but who's going to pay?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.45,0:17:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,At present, Soka Gakkai doesn't have the financial wherewithal to buy instruments.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.80,0:17:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a problem. \NWe'll make do with rented ones for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.57,0:17:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I see
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.22,0:17:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Please leave it me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.21,0:17:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.74,0:17:40.60,Sign,,0,0,0,,Several days later
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.95,0:17:40.58,Top,,0,0,0,,Oh, Arimura-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.58,0:17:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming. \NCome on in now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.59,0:17:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, is the band prepared?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.94,0:17:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Nine members agreed to participate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.11,0:17:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We borrowed the instruments from the Tsurumi neighborhood association.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.07,0:17:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All experienced performers?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.32,0:18:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, more or less.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.30,0:18:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, we have little time to rehearse... {しかし なにぶん日にちがありませんので････ - could be "because there's no fixed date..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.39,0:18:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Just some Soka Gakkai songs will suffice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.16,0:18:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it. I'll do what I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.21,0:18:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, our next problem is the costumes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.96,0:18:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.60,0:18:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the bow ties and such that musicians usually wear. What about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.11,0:18:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid we don't have anyone \Nwith a bow tie outfit...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.22,0:18:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the band's first public performance...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.14,0:18:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Get them all together.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.73,0:18:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll find the money for the costumes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.64,0:18:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not much time for practice, but I hope you can pull it together
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.81,0:18:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,by the day of the youth's climbing of Taisekiji. {lit: general mountain climbing - a ritual of coming to taisekiji}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.15,0:18:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.22,0:18:45.24,Sign,,0,0,0,,Memorial Hall, Ryogoku (formerly the Kokugikan) {両国・メモリアルホール}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.07,0:18:41.24,NarTop,,0,0,0,,On May 3rd, 30,000 representatives from across the country
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.24,0:18:45.24,NarTop,,0,0,0,,gathered to hold the 10th Spring Headquarters General Meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.24,0:18:53.24,Sign,,0,0,0,,May 3rd, 10th Headquarters General Meeting {5月3日 第10回 本部総会}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.11,0:18:53.23,NarTop,,0,0,0,,When Toda took office in May 1951, Soka Gakkai had just 1,200 households,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.67,0:18:55.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but now, three years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.46,0:18:59.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,it has expanded to 102,000 households—\Nnearly 100 times that number.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.36,0:19:06.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The desire to advance the people's religious awakening further on swept through the venue.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.75,0:19:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You might think of the Soka Gakkai spirit as a burdensome set of ideas,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.00,0:19:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's really just one—of returning to the times of Nichiren Daishonin. {学会精神というと何か面倒なことのように思うが それは「日蓮大聖人の時代に還れ」 というだけのことです}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.84,0:19:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Daishonin, driven by his deep desire to bring happiness to people,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.95,0:19:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,was able to reveal the Great Buddha Dharma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.19,0:19:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Embracing this spirit and working diligently to spread the teachings is what it truly means
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.06,0:19:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to "return to the times of Daishonin."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.45,0:19:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that by May 3rd of next year, we can all come together again,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.58,0:19:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,having found true happiness through Buddha's grace by fully refining our faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.24,0:19:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That is my only wish!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.06,0:20:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.81,0:20:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's board!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.81,0:20:13.82,Sign,,0,0,0,,Men 1\NMen 2 {男子}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.82,0:20:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Department head!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.00,0:20:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The second group of buses is running behind schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.84,0:20:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But the train group already departed from Tokyo Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.80,0:20:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.01,0:20:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Morikawa-kun, ask the bus company...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.81,0:20:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it! I'll call them and check on the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.55,0:20:34.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,The only thing I'm worried about \Nis the weather tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.23,0:20:40.84,Thought,,0,0,0,,The weather forecast calls for rain in eastern Shizuoka Prefecture... But I hope it holds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.32,0:20:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is on board!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.13,0:21:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief, it started to rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.87,0:21:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Rain?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.92,0:21:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So my worries came true, after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.39,0:21:34.40,Top,,0,0,0,,All 5,500 members of 30 male and female youth divisions have just arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.42,0:21:34.41,Sign,,0,0,0,,Rikyoubou Temple {理境坊}{https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E7%90%86%E5%A2%83%E5%9D%8A_(%E5%AF%8C%E5%A3%AB%E5%AE%AE%E5%B8%82) - one of the pagodas of taisekiji that they mentioned earlier}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.41,0:21:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They're finally here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.08,0:21:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.81,0:21:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we doing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.90,0:21:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Just give a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.90,0:21:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I heard you. \NLet's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.01,0:21:45.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The youth division began its solemn ascent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.66,0:21:52.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On May 9th, 5,500 men and women from the Youth Division gathered in the pouring rain
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.17,0:21:56.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to pledge their commitment \Nto a new beginning for the Common Path.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.67,0:22:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us, the Youth Division, solemnly vow to dedicate our lives to the fight
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.44,0:22:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for the achievement of the Common Path, under the great leadership of Toda Josei-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.99,0:22:15.27,Thought,,0,0,0,,Three years ago, on the day the Men's Youth Division was formed, it also rained heavily.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.96,0:22:17.87,Thought,,0,0,0,,Back then, Director Kiyohara said,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.46,0:22:25.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,This rain spells the challenges ahead for the Youth Division more clearly than anything else. {unsure what they mean, lit is "speak of" assumed in the sense of "foreboding"}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.13,0:22:27.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,Three years have passed...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.78,0:22:32.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,Today, the elite of 30 male and female divisions \Ngathered to announce the second beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.26,0:22:36.27,Thought,,0,0,0,,Once again, it became a ritual in the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.11,0:22:43.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,The heavens never seem to tire of reminding us how difficult the road ahead will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.21,0:22:51.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,Then it is up to us to take on the many challenges \Nthat will come our way in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.85,0:22:54.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,The unprecedented mission \Nof the Common Path
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.37,0:22:57.60,Thought,,0,0,0,,can only be accomplished by overcoming unprecedented difficulties!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.52,0:23:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason today's Youth Division meeting didn’t receive the blessing of Brahma and Sakra,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.17,0:23:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have to hold it in the pouring rain, is entirely due to my slander of the Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.54,0:23:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,For that, I offer my deepest apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.02,0:23:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.46,0:23:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that as you fight for the achievement of the Common Path
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.61,0:23:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and work to build \Na peaceful and happy Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.78,0:23:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you will always stay true to the determination and resolve you swore on this rainy day.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.20,0:23:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you do that, my friends?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.87,0:23:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.82,0:23:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai Song—Choir! \NConductor—Chief Yamamoto!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.91,0:23:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! Put your hearts into it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.41,0:23:58.79,Sign,,0,0,0,,The band's first performance after its formation at a Soka Gakkai event {音楽隊結成後、初の学会行事での演奏}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.79,0:24:07.36,Song,,0,0,0,,Born as a Japanese man, standing on the battlefield {https://bunbun.boo.jp/okera/w_shouka/t_gunka/senjin_kun1.htm}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.36,0:24:12.11,Song,,0,0,0,,Cherish your name, O man of beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.11,0:24:16.52,Song,,0,0,0,,When it is time to fall, fall gracefully,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.52,0:24:21.11,Song,,0,0,0,,Like the sakura petals that scatter across Japan
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.11,0:24:25.54,Song,,0,0,0,,Don't be arrogant about your mountainous might
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.54,0:24:29.71,Song,,0,0,0,,Our army is as flexible as the sea itself... {海をも容るる　陣をもち}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.80,0:24:30.45,NarTop,,0,0,0,,After this ceremony,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.45,0:24:38.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,President Toda proposed that the Youth Division holds another Meeting at Taisekiji in October.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.81,0:24:41.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto Shinichi and his young men and women
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.79,0:24:46.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,take on this new challenge with the goal of rallying 10,000 members.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.81,0:24:53.81,Sign,,0,0,0,,{Soka Gakkai}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.81,0:24:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,"Do not preach this Sutra to people ignorant.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.01,0:25:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are clever, keenly aware of prajna, possess great wisdom and strong vijnana..." {great wisdom in this case should also be a special buddhist term}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.81,0:25:05.46,NarTop,,0,0,0,,In response to a request from the "Lotus Sutra Study Group,"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.81,0:25:09.81,Sign,,0,0,0,,Toda's lecture to members of the University of Tokyo's "Lotus Sutra Study Group"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.46,0:25:08.04,NarTop,,0,0,0,,an intramural circle at the University of Tokyo,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.04,0:25:09.81,NarTop,,0,0,0,,Toda delivered monthly lectures
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.81,0:25:12.82,NarTop,,0,0,0,,on the Lotus Sutra to the university students.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.83,0:25:17.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,All the members had joined Soka Gakkai within the past two years
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.81,0:25:22.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and participated in daily activities as part of the Youth Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.65,0:25:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.90,0:25:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good. \NNow it's my turn to ask questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.40,0:25:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Who authored the Lotus Sutra?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.36,0:25:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Buddha!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.85,0:25:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of age are we living in?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.39,0:25:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Latter Day of the Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.39,0:25:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the greatest wisdom of our time?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.65,0:25:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... I believe it's\NNam-Myoho-Renge-Kyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.90,0:25:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! That's it. \NNow you understand, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.38,0:25:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.91,0:25:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow me to expand that thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.91,0:26:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless we make a clear distinction between Nichiren Daishonin's Buddhism,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.72,0:26:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the highest wisdom of humanity, and the Buddha's Lotus Sutra,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.41,0:26:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we won't be able to apply the essence of Buddhism to the modern age.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.92,0:26:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to grasp this parable,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.32,0:26:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to return to the basics of Nichiren Daishonin's Buddhism and study it closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.93,0:26:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you will be able to understand the Lotus Sutra with ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.50,0:26:25.19,Thought,,0,0,0,,So that's where I need to look?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.67,0:26:31.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The reason Toda, despite his busy schedule, began lecturing on the Lotus Sutra
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.04,0:26:36.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to a handful of argumentative and often critical University of Tokyo students {lit: full of logic}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.72,0:26:44.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was his early recognition of the crucial role students play in advancing the Common Path.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.78,0:26:51.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He envisioned the future success that the students he introduced to the Buddha's Law
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.01,0:26:55.00,Narrator,,0,0,0,,would achieve in the next few decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.00,0:27:01.30,Sign,,0,0,0,,Toda's lecture to representatives from each university {各大学の代表メンバーへの戸田の講義}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.53,0:27:02.57,NarTop,,0,0,0,,In the following year of 1955, the number of listeners for his Lotus Sutra lectures grew to 30,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.57,0:27:09.90,NarTop,,0,0,0,,with applicants chosen from Waseda, Keio, Nihon, Chuo, Meiji, and other universities.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.90,0:27:12.61,NarTop,,0,0,0,,This gathering would later become the basis
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.61,0:27:16.03,NarTop,,0,0,0,,for the formation of the \NSoka Gakkai Student Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.03,0:27:19.03,Sign,,0,0,0,,Haneda Airport
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.03,0:27:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We're finally going to my homeland of Hokkaido. \NDo your best while we're away, everyone. {actually "favourite; likely winner" but I think that's what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.39,0:27:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Come back soon! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.05,0:27:42.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This year's annual summer regional guidance program greatly surpassed the scale
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.66,0:27:48.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,of any previous one, with 250 representatives sent to 20 major cities nationwide.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.25,0:27:56.44,NarTop,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto Shinichi accompanied Toda to Hokkaido and visited Sapporo for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.07,0:27:58.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,Sapporo {札幌市}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.73,0:28:04.08,NarTop,,0,0,0,,Shinichi visited roundtable discussions in Sapporo and the surrounding areas,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.08,0:28:08.28,NarTop,,0,0,0,,encouraging people to join \Nand energizing the activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.63,0:28:14.63,Sign,,0,0,0,,Hokkaido Convention {北海道大会}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.44,0:28:18.15,NarTop,,0,0,0,,The regional guidance implemented across the country was an astounding success,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.15,0:28:23.16,NarTop,,0,0,0,,with the number of households converted in August hitting 12,700,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.16,0:28:26.81,NarTop,,0,0,0,,marking the first time it exceeded 10,000 households in a single month.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.53,0:28:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been wanting to show you my hometown for a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.94,0:28:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it's just some fish and scenery in the middle of nowhere, at least it's scenery to die for.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.88,0:28:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been really looking forward to visiting Atsuta from the moment I heard about it from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.78,0:28:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, does it help you grasp the vastness of the Ishikari Plain from looking at it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.73,0:28:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's really immense!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.12,0:28:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin-Chan, in a little while, we'll reach the Ishikari River.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.62,0:29:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.46,0:29:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, it's actually incredibly wide. \NIsn't it also quite deep? {actually "that's a whole lot of water" but idk what he meant by that}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.41,0:29:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, because its drainage basin is huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.41,0:29:25.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,For the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.76,0:29:30.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the teacher and student travel together to visit the teacher's hometown of Atsuta Village
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.25,0:29:36.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,"I wonder what kind of nature and climate nurtured Sensei during his upbringing..."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.03,0:29:39.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Thinking about Toda's hometown of Atsuta,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.42,0:29:45.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,which he would soon lay his eyes on, \NShinichi felt incredible lightness in his chest. {/puffed his chest out}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.37,0:30:56.33,Sign,,0,0,0,,Human Revolution \NEpisode 10\NThe End
